{
  "stem": "10644.4",
  "chunk_idx": 8,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 96,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "[LAUGHS] --it is-- my dear, the-- the-- here, during this night, you know, a Polish-- Polish prisoner were-- he was a-- comes running and throws us a piece of-- of horse's meat.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 96,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Now, horse has been for us a delicacy.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 96,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Because in this was the only-- only protein what we could get.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 96,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "It has a little taste.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 96,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "We know, because it could have so-called hippuric acid, it just-- acidity of this hippuric acid.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 96,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But otherwise, it is-- it was perfect food what our body needed.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 96,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And I recall that I took the pieces.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 96,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And in the fire, you know, fire for me and for my friend, Dr.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 96,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Kronsohn, we both have typhus.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 96,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "He has complication with the heart.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 96,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "I start to feel pains in my legs.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 96,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] Next day, we-- somebody gets out and say there is a Russian officer outside-- a Russian soldier-- true-- a Russian soldier.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 96,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And I hear tremendous amount of [NON-ENGLISH] Russian soldiers-- Russian army passing by, around 300 yards from us.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 96,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "You see a road.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 96,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "They paved the road.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 96,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And they are passing, you know, one division-- a tremendous amount.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 96,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "I was-- was thinking for that-- oh, they are coming to liberate.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 96,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "No.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 96,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "That was not the easier intentions even at interested in us.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 96,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "We were near-- they were going towards Laumberg.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 96,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "Two, three miles from Laumberg was a-- a island, Peenemunde, where all the missiles there, German missiles, V1 and V2.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 96,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "You know, at the-- end of the war, they had missiles shooting into-- into London-- were-- were built.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 96,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "And there was a-- a race between the Russians and the English, English gun coming from-- from the north, Russians coming from the-- from the east.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 96,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "Everybody wanted, you know, to grab this installations-- installations.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 96,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "The Russians grabbed it.",
      "word_count": 4
    }
  ],
